Subject: Re: [T2] valve adjustment

The simplest method is this - for each cylinder, turn the motor until
one valve is open, then adjust the other valve for that cylinder.

Do them in order or mark on paper which are done as you go.  Don't need
to look at timing marks, pullies, the rotor, or anything else.  Easy as pie.

-David

